We will be dividing the dataset with 12 columns (1 for each month) into 3 groups of 4 months representing seasons Summer, Rainy and Winter.

In [138]:
def meanOfSeason(a_dataframe, season):
    if(re.match(season, 'summer', re.I)):
        return a_dataframe[['Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun']].mean(axis = 1).tolist()
    if(re.match(season, 'rainy', re.I)):
        return a_dataframe[['Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct']].mean(axis = 1).tolist()
    if(re.match(season, 'winter', re.I)):
        return a_dataframe[['Nov', 'Dec', 'Jan', 'Feb']].mean(axis = 1).tolist()

maximumTemperature_data = pd.read_csv('data/maximumTemperature.csv', sep = '\t').head(100)

  • Calculate mean. One column for 1 season.
  • Every feature has 3 columns representing seasons.

It looks like Precipitation, wetDayFrequency, MaximumTemperature, cloudCover have good variance and can be selected. But I will be confirming by just calculating the variance along axis=1 and choose top 3 features to predict rainfall.

In [146]:
sel = VarianceThreshold()#(threshold=(.8 * (1 - .8)))
sel.fit(summer_data.as_matrix())

mask = sel.variances_ > 0.2
after_feature_selection_summer = summer_data.loc[:, mask]
after_feature_selection_summer.head()
